definition: superstructure
on top/upon/above/upper/previous/first (of multiple parts)/to climb/to get onto/to go up/to attend (class or university)

to establish/to found/to set up/to build/to construct

sentences.chinese: 上層建築保持防火巡迴檢查。

sentences.english: Democracy is part of the superstructure.
Superstructure assembly of prefabrication is new technique of ship building.

sentences.english: How does the economic base determine superstructure?

sentences.english: What kind of parallel relations do the Party, Government and Army have in the superstructure of China?

sentences.english: Hobbes built the houses and institutions.
sentences.chinese: 而霍布斯則建立了上層建築。
